HEADWORD: Shorthorn
<hw>Short"horn`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>One of a breed of
large, heavy domestic cattle having short horns. The breed was developed
in England.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

